This actor represents any member of a patient's family that may be given the profile to review or edit.

This use case allows a user to take a previously created health profile record and change the proband to another family member. The user will select an existing family member and the system will re-calcualte the familial relationships with the chosen member as the new index for the Family Health History. The system will only preserve the family members that are biologically related.

This actor is a generalized actor representing the user that is creating or editing the Family Health History Profile. The Clinician, Patient, and Patient Family Member actors inherit the capabilities of the generalized User actor.
Create or Edit Family Health History

This user story allows a user to input personal data and health history for the proband. THis is required before a family history can be created. The following personal information is requested for the proband, followed by the personal health history.
  • Name (Text Field)
  • Date of Birth (Numeric Text Field, dd/mm/yyyy)
  • Biological Gender (M or F)
  • Weight in lbs. (Numeric Text )
  • Height (2 Numeric Text fields for feet and inches)
  • Ethnicity (user will select from pre-defined values)
  • Race (user will select from pre-defined values)
  • Consangunity
NOTE: The Living Flag, though not dsplayed, needs to be set as "Y" NOTE: Only the name, DoB, and Gender are required The user can then associate a disease with this family member. (See Associate Disease with Family Member user story.)
Create or Edit Family Health History

The system should display a list of all default diseases that are tracked in the system, as defined by the enumerated Disease type table in the Domain Model. If the user marks as suffering from a disease, and the disease has branches, the sub-disease(s) will be shown. By selecting a diseases the user is saying that it is an affliction, so there is no need to ask if afflicted or not. The following are the data fields that needed to be completed for each applicable disease/sub-disease:
  • Age at Onset (If afflicted, need to select from a set of ranges as specified in the enumerated Age Range table in the Domain Model).

In order to edit a profile, the user must first find a Family Health History (XML file) in their local environment and upload it to the application. The system then opens the profile and allows the user to edit it.
If the user loads a Family Health History that has a different structure than that generated by the system, the system will try and read as much of the data as possible, but if it is unable to, it will notify the user and prompt to choose another file.

UML:TaggedValue.value:
This use case enables a user to create a new FHH profile by entering medical health history for his- or herself and relevant family members. A user may also edit an existing profile by first uploading an existing profile that was created by the application back into the application
Once completed, the Patient can extend this use case to view a pedigree diagram of the health history, download a graphical representation of the model, or download an XML version of the profile to local media.
It should be noted that the system does not store or persist any data, all data is downloaded and stored in the user's environment.

UML:TaggedValue.value: Create or Edit Family Health History

This user story allows a user to enter for one or more family members, by filling in the following for each entry created:
  • Name of Individual or Family Member
  • Biological Sex
  • Relationship (User should choose from a pre-determined list. If relationship is cousin, need to be able to assign the appropriate aunt/uncle as the parent; if half bro/sis, need to assign the appropriate parent)
  • Living Flag (y or N)
  • Age ( Only if Living Flag is Y; The system will prompt for the DoB or an approximate age (3 digit numeric value). The system will translate this to the year of birth)
  • Age at Death (only valid if Living Flag N; user will select a range of ages)
  • Cause of Death (only valid if Living Flag N, user will select from a pre-defined values and have the option of selecting other or unknown. If other, the user may input a free-text entry)
  • Multiple Birth (Y or N Flag)
  • Identical or Fraternal (Flag, Only if Multiple-Birth is Y)
  • Consanguinity
NOTE: Relationship is the only required field. The user can then associate a disease with this family member. (See Associate Disease with Family Member user story.)

This user story allows a user to customize the chart/table by selecting which diseases and/or family members to display and include. The user will have the option to create a chart, diagram, or a chart and diagram. Within the diagram, the user will be able to choose which diseases to highlight, and can assign abbreviations to the non-standard diseases that have been added.

This user story allows a user to download a read-only version of the chart and/or table to their local media so that it can be shared with others for viewing purposes. Any prson viewing the data should be able to copy the data to be used in another application.

In this user story the user wants to view a graphical representation of the pedigree chart and/or a table on the computer screen they are working on. If the chart is large, the user must be able to scroll vertically or horizontally to see the entire chart.

This is a system use case which creates a pedigree chart of the family health history based on the selected profile. The user can select to limit the profile to select disease(s), or view all. The user can choose to view a chart that includes a diagram (pedigree chart) and information in tabular format, or just the data in a tabular format.
This user story allows the user wants to print the pedigree chart and/or the table on a local printer. The user must be able to print the entire chart.

EAScenario.name: User Story - Change Proband
EAScenario.description:
In this user story a family member wants to take an existing profile and edit it so that they become the proband and the system automatically adjusts the relationships to reflect the change.
When the user first changes the proband, the system checks to see if the relationship is a sibling or not. If it is, the system utilizes the existing data for all relationships.

EAScenario.name: Autocomplete Data Entry
EAScenario.description: This user story allows the user to select from a list of pre-determined diseases that are available in the system, when one of the standard displayed diseases do not meet their needs. As the user types a value in the text field to add, the application will display a list of values matching the entered string for the user to select from. The system will look to match the input value against any portion of the pre-existing diseases, not just a beginning text search.
